values:
soooooo.. i've narrowed my choices for the english project down to two!

BLOG - basically i have to comment on each of the major units we've covered since september on a xanga or whatever in "a lucid and original way"
POETRY - write 10 original war-themed poems with the audience being servicemen in the US Army fighting in Iraq

i think that the poems is, if you look at it, kinda easy. i mean, poetry can be however long or short you want it to be right? so i can practically BS the whole thing and still get a good grade, or not, because it's all based on interpretation. blogging would take up a lot more time in comparison. however, blogging fits more into my lifestyle. i mean, i don't mind blogging and rambling about my thoughts on certain things. i also have somewhat of an idea of how i'd portray each section that we've covered. going more into depth about my thoughts on these things.. for the poems, i don't know if i can really BS the whole thing because i don't really have a perspective on war or what it's like for the army. and i guess if i chose that project that's part of the work that's needed - to research army life and what not. also, i don't know how much material i would have for ten poems. really the only experience of war that i have is that with my parents lol. so yeah. i need help. please help me.

soooo.. for josan, i'm updating! be happy =p also, i'm bored and waiting for the time to pass. why, you may i ask? hahaha i'll tell you why eventually..
wow, i really haven't logged in here in the longest time. the layout is so crappy T____T i must change it.. eventually..
spring break has not felt like a break at all. i've been busy busy busy. i really don't even remember much of what happened last week. it feels like it's been so long ago!

April 17, 2006
9:30 - 12:30 driving classes
yes, driving classes, my dears because i've been a bum and haven't taken them yet. so, yay for driving around newark and maplewood lol

April 18, 2006
COLUMBIA COLLEGE VISIT
my goodness, Columbia is so amazingly beautiful. i went with kristine and our moms. the ride there was spent with mostly our moms talking about random stuff but as soon as we got into new york the scenery was just.. wow..
the info-session and tour made me want to go to Columbia sooooo badly, however, my grades and requirements probably won't make the cut. i can still dream, right? i'm unsure of whether or not i should apply early decision to Columbia or NYU. i guess it all depends on how the NYU visit goes..
anyway, our tour was a chibi filipina. she was from TX and was very thorough and informative throughout the tour. the place was very college-y and i <3 it.

April 19, 2006
SETON HALL COLLEGE VISIT
my mom and i went on the 10:00 am info-session and tour to Seton Hall. it's an okay school and i guess it's more of a likely school for me. apparently it's really easy to commute from Seton to NYC so it'd be okay if i wanted some internships in the city etc. they had a speech-language pathologist booth towards the end of the tour and i totally signed up for information. ever since stanko's girlfriend visited our linguistics class i've been inclined to take speech-language pathology as my major. according to.. i forgot her name, so i'll just call her mrs. stanko lol.. anyway, according to her, Kean, Seton Hall, TCNJ, and i think Montclair State have good speech-language pathology courses. i think she mentioned Rutgers did, too, but i don't remember. and apparently the NYU SLP course isn't as good as the others because that's where they place the rejects from the other schools.. but hey, if i suck that much maybe i will get into NYU because of that. hah...
after the Seton Hall visit my mom and i went to UMDNJ to drop of keys for my idiot dad who locked his own in the car. -_- we stayed there for lunch and i had sushi and a fruit cup. on my way out of there i saw a sign that lead to "speech-language pathology" and pointed it out to my mom who was skeptical about SLP being a successful or popular job etc. so she's going to ask around the hospital about how much speech-language pathologists get and what not when she goes back to work.

start chem homework?
HAHAHA, that was funny. my plan with kristine was to go out to the movies and stuff. sooo, as an excuse i'd go to her house then we'd go out. so much for that. it seems like a lot of my plans to hang out with people have been thwarted all this week. ahh well. when i got home from UMD i asked my mom if i could go to kristine's house to do chem hw [ which i intended to start there ]. so around 5 or 6 i went and ended up not even looking at chem. first, i was helping kris stuff boxes for her party favors. then, it was getting hot in her room so i suggested we go to magic fountain and invite victor, too, lol. so kristine and i left and waited for victor at her bro's hwa rang do school across the street. damn, matt's so into the whole thing compared to kris' bro who was yawning during the 10 minute dance workout. kris and i met this korean girl, master yum's niece, kristine or christine. master yum said that she's on the PGA tour and i was wondering if she was that amazing asian golfer girl on TV. she did look like her... i don't know her name though, so yeah.
well, eventually victor came an hour later so we went to magic fountain and got our usuals. kris' mom called and asked when we were going to come back and kris told her that victor just got there. lol, kris' mom is soooo funny.. nakakatuwa siya. i wish i had a mom that approved of my guy friends and was humorous about the whole guy situation. eventually, all of us, kris, me, rj, and victor went back to kris' house. tita marge asked me to play the piano and i pushed on that victor was so much better than me [ really, he is... ]. so tita marge tells victor to play for her so she can judge if he's worthy or not lol. victor plays and blows her off while she complains that kris and i don't practice enough. so kris and i attempt to play our duet from last year's recital and embarrass ourselves horribly. basically we all just had a mini-piano concert for kris' mom until i left. *sigh* they're so cute. while i was playing tita marge, kris, and victor were sitting on the couch together and it was just..  awww.. my mom's so not cool -_-

April 20, 2006
10:00 - 1:00 driving classes
yay!! i finally got my permit!! i practiced for maybe 2 hours at i think Weequahic Park in newark parallel parking and k-turning. ugh.. i got so hot and sweaty from the nervousness and the heat. i feel accomplished though, so that's good =)

2:00 - 5:00 calc/chem homework @ westfield library
so christina and i decided to meet up at WML to attempt homework and what not. we started doing calc and we were going along well doing our 45 minute practice AP test. then we lost all hope of ever passing calc and went on to chem. well, eventually we just gave up and just talked. heh.. the mafia's name should probably changed to the "azn heartbreakers". we're awesome. yes.
christina left around 5 and i waited for my mom. she came and let me drive us home ^__^  yayness. i was excited. and nervous. my mom said i was good!! so i drove us to and from the chapel later on as well and did a good job again!! i'm so exicted to drive now lol. i wouldn't mind going out with her now as long as i can drive. teeheehee.

April 21, 2006
soooo.. finally to today!! i woke up at about 6 and couldn't go back to sleep because i'm so excited! today i'm visiting NYU with my mom, christina, and rob. christina's picking my mom and me up and dropping us off at the elizabeth station at around 9:00 am and hopefully we'll meet rob from his linden train at 9:22. i've been planning this for soooo long and it's finally come! well, first we're going to visit Fordham for the 10:00 info-session and tour then hopefully catch the 2:30 NYU info-session and tour. my mom tried to reserve spots for us around last week but the NYU people said that all of their info-sessions were booked for this week. so originally we were just gonna meet up with one of my friend's from there and she'd tour us around. but then rob told me that ariyan visited without having registered for the specific date he visited and it was okay. so late last night i went online and signed us all up for the info-session on monday just in case lol. so yeah, we're gonna try to go to the info-session at 2:30 - 4:30 and at around 5 we'll meet up with becky, my pingry buddayy! we'll probably get back home late at night..

April 22, 2006
hmm.. i really don't know what's gonna happen tomorrow. well, if all goes according to plan today i'll be able to go to the Yankee game with rob, kris, and victor. lol, i don't know how that's gonna work out but i hope it will.. i've been looking forward to this all break. *sigh*

so yeah, that's my spring break!! so busy.. i really haven't gotten much rest. i've been watching naruto probably almost every day and i'm still only on episode 101! rawrr i'm so far behind compared to alaa and josan. here are just some future dates i'm looking forward to..
April 29, 2006 - Sakura Matsuri [ Cherry Blossom Festival ] @ Brooklyn Botanic Garden
May 13, 2006 - multi-cultural fair! look for me at the bubble tea booth with kirk and tara!! i'm gonna be making some really sweet bubble tea =)
June 16 - 18, 2006 - animeNEXT with EVERYONE lol

yeah, those are the only major things i could think of so far.. i think they're the only things that can get me through the rest of the school year. i might be taking an EMT course at the Clark Volunteer Squad over the summer if my mom'll let me. so yay for community service hours!

well i should really get going and take a shower since it's been an hour since i've started writing this crap. bye bye for now!!

"Do you love someone because you were kissed by him?
It isn`t love, it`s interiority complex.
Are your palms sweaty, is your heart racing and is your voice caught within your chest?
It isn`t love, it`s like.
You can`t keep your eyes off of them, am I right?
It isn`t love, it`s lust.
Do you love someone because you can`t live without their touch?
It`s not love, it`s lust.
Are you proud and eager to show them off?
It isn`t love, it`s luck.
Do you want them because you know they`re there?
It isn`t love, it`s loneliness.
Do you stay for their confessions of love, because you don`t want to hurt them?
It isn`t love, it`s pity.
Do you belong to them because their sight makes your heart skip a beat?
It isn`t love, it`s infatuation.
Do you think he or she is really gorgeous?
It isn`t love, it`s infatuation.
Do you pardon their faults because you care about them?
It isn`t love, it`s friendship.
Do you share everything with them?
It isn`t love, it`s friendship.
Do you tell them that they are the only one you think of?
It isn`t love, it`s a lie.
Are you willing to give all of your favorite things for their sake?
It isn`t love, it`s charity.
Would you sacrifice your own life for them?
It isn`t love, it`s heroism.
If you love someone because you think that you shouldn`t leave him because others think that you shouldn`t...
It isn`t love, it`s compromise.
Do you know you love them because you simply cannot live without them?
It isn`t love, it`s dependency.
Does your heart ache and break, do you cry for their pain, even when they`re strong?
Then it`s love.
Do their eyes see your true heart, and touch your soul so deeply it hurts?
Then it`s love.
Would you allow them to leave you, not because they want to but because they have to?
Then it`s love."

so life's really been treating me fairly nowadays. school has been way too much of a hassle and i feel like i just died today. there's just way too much crap teachers are piling up on us and it's only the beginning of the marking period! i hate my physics group, no offense. i feel like i did so much during that period without much help. it gave me such a bad headache that i couldn't study for the english test. grawr. thankfully i'm going on that french/spanish club trip tomorrow. i can't take another day of school!

i've been so much more active in church right now and i'm happy about it. i still feel kinda left out with everyone else. last night was so bad for me emotionally. at MGEM practice kim brought in the scrapbook she made for kai and i was just wishing i had friends like that. close close friends like kai. they were together since they were little kids but that's only a dream of mine. i haven't had any really close friends that i can completely trust and turn to and that my parents approve of either. even in that horoscope email thing it said that the number of real close friends i have in my lifetime would only be six. that's true i guess, but i really need just someone to understand me completely right now. but what can i do? all i can do is to turn to God to comfort me.

mango..first snow of the season. =DDD so pretty yet so freakishly annoying. let's see..i left school at 3 and got home around 5:45. yurp..well, we had a few stop overs. julia came with me luckily. if she didn't she wouldn't have gotten a ride home cuz i heard that the hillside bus never came to votech/magnet. crap..that sucks..we went on route 22 cuz my dad wanted to buy a new shovel. we passed by blinds to go to pick up our blinds and then we went to home depot and walmart but no shovel!! mango..sucks. mommy also wanted me to buy her gloves but i couldn't find the ones she wanted!! they were all expensive and ugly-ish and there wasn't that great of a selection at walmart. we took a 'shortcut' home cuz 22 was really traffic-y but we were stuck there for about 30ish minutes. turns out there were two accidents on the way home. dropped of julia and went home. good news though!!..kinda..all my plans for this weekend are cancelled due to the snow!! so my weekend's NOT booked! general choir practice was cancelled for today, sadly..first ever general practice cancelled..my voice concert tomorrow is cancelled as well as my piano recital on sunday. yay!!! i'm freeeeee!!! ohh yeah, maude, i've been trying to call you about it!!! anyway, i'll possibly go to the movies with christina tomorrow if she didn't change her mind. if not, maybe with kristine?? yeahh..watch HONEY!! jessica alba =DDD pretty pretty snow. first snow of the season. beautiful. luckily i dressed for the occasion. someone reminded me about it too =) yup, i was ready!! wore my scarf, insulated windbreakers, and timbs!! so totally ready!! -simplicity is beauty-

do i seem superficial to you? i'm so vague about
so many things. it always looks like i'm happy and
so optimistic, right? what's beyond this exterior
of mine? am i hurting? am i sad? sometimes i
ask myself the same question. am i just pretending
to be strong for the benefit of others? that's how
i feel sometimes..but then when i pretend to be
happy and eventually make them happy, i get happy

can't breathe right. i wanna go home..

<font face="arial">wow..people are really depressed or getting depressed lately. i look at some of my friends' xangas or ljs and it's all about depression, sadness, pain. i feel so bad for them, but i don't know what to do. i don't know what words to say or if it'll even help them at all. i was kinda lucky to have gone through my depression stage with some of my friends behind me. 'the journal' if anyone gets that..but i guess i kinda passed that stage of depression in this part of my life..everyone with 'the journal' got through it..and i think we're better people know. we're stronger and used to being disappointed and sad. i just got tired of hating myself for certain things that happened in the past and despising myself for my qualities that i disliked. i'm so tired of complaining about life. i remembered that i would push people away when i got depressed. i never wanted anyone to know how i felt and because of that, i missed out on so much. 

i remember there was just so much depression at one point that i kept on thinking about taking away my life. i felt so alone, like no one was there for me, but it was my own fault. i pushed them away. and now i know that suicide is not right. God gave us life and it was his gift unto us and we shouldn't take it for granted. there are so many people that i've seen, heard, or read about, that couldn't continue carrying on. it's sad really, the various stories of how and why they decided to end their lives..they don't know what's out there. they can't see the beauty of life behind their own shadows of the past and present. they live only now and they can't see dreams come true. 

after pessimism came optimism for me. i try not to dwell in the past anymore. it's my past, everyone's haunted by their past, but just because it happened, it doesn't mean that it can haunt you forever. people can change their present and look to a better future. sounds stupid, i know, but it's true..

i've been thinking a lot about my name description from kabalarians:
[here's what it said..just in case you don't want to look all the way down to the entry]
>>The name of Steffanie has created a congenial nature with the desire to associate in friendship and understanding both socially and in the business world. Peaceful and settled conditions appeal to you and you are naturally desirous of having the security of a home, where your life could follow a definite pattern, and where you would not have to make major decisions. You find it difficult to take a definite stand, partly because you lack confidence, and also because you dislike any issues which create dissension between people. Procrastination is a weakness of your nature, causing an inability always to complete your plans or to concentrate for long. You need to see a concept presented completely in detail before you can understand it, and if you cannot understand it, you come to your own conclusion and often fail to listen to and reason out another's point of view. You resist being forced into change and could become almost impervious to new ideas. You desire refinement, understanding, and appreciation, yet sometimes your outward attitude does not reveal your innermost feelings, and thus you have never felt truly understood. Your name has given you a desire for heavy, rich foods, which cause sluggish digestion. You could suffer with constipation, stomach, or intestinal disorders, or disturbances in the fluid functions of the body.<<
i think the whole thing is practically true. i like to make friends 'both socially and in the business world.' and about 'peaceful and settled conditions' and 'the security of a home,' that is true too. i don't like it when people argue ["you dislike any issues which create dissension between people"], especially my parents. i can't stand it when they yell at each other. when i grow up and start my own family, i seriously imagine myself with a filipino man..someone, preferably, who grew up in the philippines and knows tagalog. i love my culture and i want to pass it down to my own children and remind them of their roots so that they'll be proud to be who they are.
i do lack confidence in myself and i'm afraid to make decisions on my own. if a question is asked in class and i'm unsure of the answer, i just don't answer at all. i don't feel confident that i might know it and then i get ashamed if i'm wrong.
the part about procrastination is way on too. i usually finish my assignments for school and piano at the last minute and the part about trouble understanding new concepts..i mean WOW. i hate change, i shouldn't, but i do..or at least i try to keep things the same. i resist it, same thing. i can deal with it and everything-death, people entering and leaving my life, being in different environments-but before i can deal with it, i worry about it. i dread the day it comes, but after it passes, it doesn't bother me much..i just usually try to avoid it i guess because i want to avoid the pain of knowing that what i'm used to might be gone.
no one understands me really..and that's right. i can only think of maybe a handful of people who might understand why i do what i do, say what i say, etc. but still, they don't know so many things about me. i usually find myself being the consoler rather than the speaker. it's also hard for me to trust someone until they trust me. i get close to people by them first opening up to me that kinda goes with the appreciation part. they appreciate me because they trust me with how they feel and rely on me. i don't know why it's that way, but that's the way it happens. i don't really approve of it cuz the relationship between two friends shouldn't be like that, but it's like that with me. if they open up to me, i might just open up to them little by little. i guess i also fear the pain of being teased or betrayed by unreliable people.
dang..this thing is getting me depressed. i need to stop thinking, but my mind is just so stubborn..it can't stop. all these things bother me so much. whenever i feel like this and have so much on my mind, i want to tell someone, but then this usually occurs when no one is really available. next time i get the opportunity to talk to someone, the feeling passes and i back out on spilling out my past feelings. i'm also afraid to pass my burdens to other people while they have their own problems to tend to..so i continue going on my own..alone..
